# Current Wealth - Destitute
Wealth Level Perk / Armor, Shields, and Weapons		SOURCEPAGE:p.184	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Destitute Equipment		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTDestitute																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:Even if pristine to start with, any armor, shields, or weapons you pick up will shortly be in horrible shape. Half AC bonus from armor and shields (minimum +1 apiece), weapons get -2 to hit and damage.
Wealth Level Perk / Magical Items				SOURCEPAGE:p.184	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Destitute Magic		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTDestitute																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:You might possess a single charm, provided that something weird is going on.
Wealth Level Perk / Mounts, Pets, and Familiars		SOURCEPAGE:p.184	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Destitute Companions	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTDestitute																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:Any mount you can lay your hands on gets -5 move, one-half normal HP, and a -3 on all rolls. As far as pets and familiars go, you could probably manage a rat or something.
Wealth Level Perk / Recognition				SOURCEPAGE:p.184	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Destitute Recognition	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTDestitute																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:Even people who know you are likely to pretend they don't. Anyone at this wealth level gains a +2 circumstance modifier to Disguise and Knowledge: Local.
Wealth Level Perk / Training					SOURCEPAGE:p.184	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Destitute Training		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTDestitute																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:Training: +2 Skill points per level gained at this wealth rank in any of skills listed above; -2 on any two chosen attributes due to illness/hunger exposure/ etc while the character remains at this wealth level.

# Current Wealth - Poor
Wealth Level Perk / Armor, Shields, and Weapons		SOURCEPAGE:p.185	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Poor Equipment		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTPoor																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:There really isn't any money to spare for this; staves, slings, clubs, improvised spears, and work knives, are about the limit. You can usually get someone to make up a crude suit of padded armor for you. Your best bet is to try to join the militia; that'll get you some basic gear, such as leather armor, spear, shortsword, small wooden shield, and a few javelins along with the training to use them effectively.
Wealth Level Perk / Magical Items				SOURCEPAGE:p.185	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Poor Magic			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTPoor																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:One minor, and usually utilitarian, charm. Fire- and light- stones, healing charms, minor enhanced tools, and other handy items are the most common.
Wealth Level Perk / Mounts, Pets And Familiars		SOURCEPAGE:p.185	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Poor Companions		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTPoor																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:Any animals you have are going to either be common, inexpensive working beasts or sources of food. Ferrets are useful, if a bit pungent. A pack-ox or horse is possible, a real mount is unlikely.
Wealth Level Perk / Acquaintances				SOURCEPAGE:p.185	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Poor Aquaintances		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTPoor																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:Guildmembers, past employers, and possibly a few members of the local underworld. If you really need an assistant, you may be able to manage an apprentice, impressionable kid, or one of your relatives.
Wealth Level Perk / Training					SOURCEPAGE:p.185	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Poor Training			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTPoor																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:Any character who levels while at this wealth level gains +2 SP to be spent on Profession, Craft, Bluff, or Gather Information, but it's rare for an adventurer to spend much time at this level.

# Current Wealth - Common
Wealth Level Perk / Armor, Shields, and Weaponry	SOURCEPAGE:p.186	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Common Equipment		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTCommon																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:You can afford light armor, shields, common, inexpensive, weapons (shortswords, short bows, javelins, etc) and equipment of ordinary quality.
Wealth Level Perk / Magical Items				SOURCEPAGE:p.186	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Common Magic			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTCommon																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:Normally three minor "charms." At least at first, these will usually be utilitarian, but the definition of "utilitarian" can vary a good deal depending on the character's background.
Wealth Level Perk / Mounts, Pets, and Familiars		SOURCEPAGE:p.186	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Common Companions		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTCommon																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:You can obtain common animals, a light riding horse (likely a bit long in the tooth, but serviceable) and a healthy mutt to act as a guard dog. "Noble" animals, including hawks, purebred hounds, hunting cats, warhorses and exotic imports, are still out of reach.
Wealth Level Perk / Retainers					SOURCEPAGE:p.186	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Common Retainers		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTCommon																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:You may have a house- or errand-boy and know an old woman or man who purports to be a witch. For the most part you won't know anyone the least bit important.
Wealth Level Perk / Training					SOURCEPAGE:p.186	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Common Training		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTCommon																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:Any character who levels while at this wealth level gains no special benefits, and suffers no unusual penalties.

# Current Wealth - Well Off
Wealth Level Perk / Armor, Shields, and Weapons		SOURCEPAGE:p.186	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Well Off Equipment		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWellOff																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:You can afford full plate armor, exotic weapons, longbows and specialized equipment. Still, at least for the time, masterwork equipment remains out of reach.
Wealth Level Perk / Magical Items				SOURCEPAGE:p.186	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Well Off Magic		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWellOff																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:Three charms and one talisman.
Wealth Level Perk / Mounts, Pets, and Familiars		SOURCEPAGE:p.186	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Well Off Companions		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWellOff																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:You can afford high quality common animals, trained warhorses, and so on. Exotic imports are still simply too expensive.
Wealth Level Perk / Retainers					SOURCEPAGE:p.186	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Well Off Retainers		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWellOff																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:You may have a single extremely loyal assistant, guard, or henchman, connections with assorted skilled professionals in various fields and a dozen or so ordinary employees. While these usually won't be going on adventures, they make life a lot easier most of the time.
Wealth Level Perk / Training					SOURCEPAGE:p.186	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Well Off Training		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWellOff																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:Any character who levels while at this wealth level gains no special benefits, and suffers no unusual penalties.

# Current Wealth - Affluent
Wealth Level Perk / Armor, Shields, and Weapons		SOURCEPAGE:p.187	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Affluent Equipment		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTAffluent																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:Are all treated as being "masterwork." The character can readily afford to buy specialized equipment from high-quality crafters.
Wealth Level Perk / Legal Privileges			SOURCEPAGE:p.187	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Affluent Legal		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTAffluent																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:Characters at this level enjoy a good deal of leeway about things like the use of deadly force against an "attacker," carrying armor, shields, and weapons, or riding in the city streets, and will virtually always get the benefit of the doubt unless the other side is even richer. It's also almost impossible to drive you insane; you're usually limited to eccentric.
Wealth Level Perk / Mounts, Pets, and Familiars		SOURCEPAGE:p.187	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Affluent Companions		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTAffluent																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:You can afford exotic pets, like fine hawks and rare imported animals. Trained warbeasts, chargers, and packtrains are at your disposal.
Wealth Level Perk / Magical Items				SOURCEPAGE:p.187	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Affluent Magic		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTAffluent																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:Five charms and two talismans.
Wealth Level Perk / Retainers					SOURCEPAGE:p.187	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Affluent Retainers		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTAffluent																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:You may have a couple of competent and loyal guards and assistants, possibly connections with an eccentric hedge wizard or minor priest (these are often related to you, and prone to sending you on odd missions or having weird visions), and quite a few employees and general gofers.
Wealth Level Perk / Skill Bonuses				SOURCEPAGE:p.187	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Affluent Skill Bonuses	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTAffluent																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:Characters who level at this wealth level gain an extra skill point each time.

# Current Wealth - Wealthy
Wealth Level Perk / Armor/Shields				SOURCEPAGE:p.187	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Equipment		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:Treat armor as one category lighter for movement and special ability purposes. This applies to shields as far as proficiencies go. Add a +2 Wealth AC bonus to shields and armor and improve the Armor Check Penalty (if any) by 2.
Wealth Level Perk / Legal Privileges			SOURCEPAGE:p.187	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Legal			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:At this point you're virtually above the law; having the resources to fund private armies tends to have that effect. Those with grievances usually resort to outlaw tactics or even larger armies.
Wealth Level Perk / Magical Items				SOURCEPAGE:p.187	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Magic			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:Seven charms and three talismans.
Wealth Level Perk / Mounts, Pets, and Familiars		SOURCEPAGE:p.187	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Companions		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:Mounts gain 2d4 levels of Magical Beast, +1d3 to each attribute, and +5' to Move. Pets and Familiars gain 1d4 levels of Magical Beast, +1d2 to each attribute, and +5' to Move.																																										
Wealth Level Perk / Recognition				SOURCEPAGE:p.187	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Recognition		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:Anyone at this level of wealth will be widely known, influential in the community and often "on call." With power comes authority - and a great deal of responsibility unless the character opts to become a hermit.
Wealth Level Perk / Retainers					SOURCEPAGE:p.187	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Retainers		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:You often have a hedge wizard or minor priest, a sage or scholar (if desired), some bodyguards and agents, and an assortment of craftsmen and ordinary employees numbering up to the hundreds at this level. Standard d20, you may have a dozen wizards.
Wealth Level Perk / Skill Bonuses				SOURCEPAGE:p.187	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Skill			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:+2 nameless bonus to Diplomacy, Gather Information, and Intimidate, thanks to the use of cash and high-quality gear. Masterwork tools and reference material (for knowledge-based skills) is presumed wherever it is useful.
Wealth Level Perk / Training					SOURCEPAGE:p.187	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Training		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:Superb. You gain +2 SP and +1 HP per level gained while this template applies, and a +2 to any single attribute (total, not per level).
Wealth Level Perk / Weapons					SOURCEPAGE:p.187	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Weapons		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:Your weaponry gains +2 built-in Wealth bonuses. It may be made of adamantine, silver, or of exotic materials as desired. Wealth bonuses stack with magical enhancement.

# Current Wealth - Imperial
Wealth Level Perk / Armor/Shields				SOURCEPAGE:p.188	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial Equipment		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:Treat as one category lighter for movement and special ability purposes, half the usual weight, with +3 AC Wealth bonus, and -3 on Armor Check Penalty (if any).
Wealth Level Perk / Magical Items				SOURCEPAGE:p.188	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial Magic		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:Seven charms and three talismans.
Wealth Level Perk / Mounts, Pets, and Familiars		SOURCEPAGE:p.188	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial Companions		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:Mounts gain 3d4 levels of Magical Beast, +1d4 to each attribute, and +10' to Move. Pets and Familiars gain 1d4+2 levels of Magical Beast, +1d3 to each attribute, and +10' to Move.
Wealth Level Perk / Recognition				SOURCEPAGE:p.188	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial Recognition	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:You will be widely recognized and will have a lot of calls on your time. Adventurers will be expected to deal with major menaces, organize the defense of the realm, and similar things. You're above the law.
Wealth Level Perk / Retainers					SOURCEPAGE:p.188	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial Retainers		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:You gain a competent mage, a skilled priest, and superb scholars and advisors, as well as an assortment of "special agents," accountants, servants, skilled craftsmen, bodyguards, and ordinary employees. This presumes that powerful spellcasters are relatively rare. In many d20 worlds you may command the services of whole academies of mages and temples full of clerics.
Wealth Level Perk / Skill Bonuses				SOURCEPAGE:p.188	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial Skill		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:You gain a +4 Wealth bonus to Diplomacy, Gather Information, and Intimidate, thanks to the ready availability of cash and the finest gear. You are assumed to have masterwork equipment whenever it would help you (and you have equipment at all), including superb reference works for knowledge-based skills.
Wealth Level Perk / Training					SOURCEPAGE:p.188	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial Training		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:The finest. +2 SP and +2 HP per level gained while this template applies. The character also gains a +2 wealth bonus to any one attribute while at this wealth level and a +10%% experience bonus.
Wealth Level Perk / Weapons					SOURCEPAGE:p.188	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial Weapons		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:All your weaponry gains a +4 innate Wealth bonus and may be made of adamantine, silver, or exotic materials as you desire.


