Enchantment / Artificer					SOURCEPAGE:p.131	KEY:Enchantment ~ Artificer				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.EnchantmentFeatChoice									DESC:You may reduce the GP or XP cost of making devices of this type by 50%%. The time required does not change.
Enchantment / Artisan					SOURCEPAGE:p.131	KEY:Enchantment ~ Artisan				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.EnchantmentFeatChoice									DESC:You may double the GP cost of creating an item to eliminate the XP cost or vice versa. Either option doubles the time required.
Enchantment / Bonded					SOURCEPAGE:p.131	KEY:Enchantment ~ Bonded				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.EnchantmentFeatChoice									DESC:Spells from the item use the wielder's caster level and attribute modifiers if those are better than its own. This usually increases the sale price by 20%%; it does not increase the base cost for making an item.
Enchantment / Excellence				SOURCEPAGE:p.131	KEY:Enchantment ~ Excellence				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.EnchantmentFeatChoice									DESC:Your items use your full attribute bonus to determine the DC of saving against them rather than the minimum required to cast the spell. This usually increases the sale price by 10%%, it does not increase the base cost for making an item.
Enchantment / Fabrication				SOURCEPAGE:p.131	KEY:Enchantment ~ Fabrication				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.EnchantmentFeatChoice									DESC:You may increase the divisor used to determine how long it takes to make items by +2000 GP. This option may be taken repeatedly.
Enchantment / Living Magic				SOURCEPAGE:p.131	KEY:Enchantment ~ Living Magic			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.EnchantmentFeatChoice									DESC:You may enchant living or undead creatures, including your own flesh and blood. This can also embed magic in words, ideas, songs, computer programs, and other intangible "items". Use-activated spells embedded in creatures are usually used by them at will or activate when triggered. Words are spoken, songs sung, and ideas concentrated on. You may transfer intangible items to other characters. The original character may still know the song, word, or idea, but it will no longer possess any power.
Enchantment / Multiple					SOURCEPAGE:p.131	KEY:Enchantment ~ Multiple				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.EnchantmentFeatChoice									DESC:You may place multiple spell formulas in the same item, although all must use the same caster level. The cost is based on the highest level spell used plus 75%% of the value of the next highest level spell plus 50%% of the value of any other spells used. You may reduce the cost of a particular spell by increasing the number of charges it costs to use (2 for half cost, 3 for one third, etc, up to a limit of 5 for one fifth).

